.TH "LIGHTNING-OFFER" 1 "May 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-offer \- BOLT-12 offers (create + pay)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning offer
[\fIsubcommand\fR] [\fIargs\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.nf
lightning offer — BOLT-12 offers (create + pay).

Implements: BOLT-12 per FEAT-173.
  share/doc/lightning/standards/bolts/12-offer-encoding.md

Subcommands:
  create <sat>|any <description> [--qr]
  pay <bolt12-offer> [<sat>] [--message <text>]
.fi
.SH USAGE
.nf
usage: lightning offer <subcommand> [args]

   BOLT-12 offers — reusable invoices. A single offer string can
   be paid many times; each payer fetches a fresh BOLT-12 invoice
   on the wire. Requires clightning ≥ 22.11 with
   experimental-offers enabled. See
   share/doc/lightning/standards/bolts/12-offer-encoding.md.
   Each sub-command also accepts --help.

subcommands:
   create <sat>|any <description> [--qr]
   pay <bolt12-offer> [<sat>] [--message <text>]
.fi
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR lightning (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Part of the \fBlightning\fR educational Lightning Network frontend.
